A layered paper collage illustration made entirely from cut pieces of colored construction paper.

Parte superiore: A paper port on the left, built from grey and off-white rectangular paper pieces — dock, crane, warehouse. A small paper ship with a black hull and blue paper sail sits at the dock, labeled "Vault" with a tiny cut-paper tag. From the ship, two separate strips of blue paper extend to the right, representing two sea routes — one labeled "CRT" and the other "KEY" with small paper labels.

Parte centrale: Above the two blue paper routes, three small paper structures float like pilot houses or control towers. The first (grey paper, labeled "VSO") stands over the first route but has a cut-paper "X" over it. The second (red paper accent, labeled "Kyverno") stands between both routes but has a tilted paper panel — incomplete. The third (blue paper, labeled "ESO") extends a single grey paper gangplank that bridges both routes together.

Parte inferiore: The two blue paper strips merge into a single wider blue paper band near the right edge. A paper Kubernetes logo (simple steering wheel shape from black paper) sits at the right edge, receiving the merged route. A small black paper hand on the ESO tower points toward the merged path.

Paper-craft details: All shapes have visible paper fiber texture and slightly rounded scissor-cut edges. Soft uniform drop shadows under every paper layer. Matte construction paper finish — no gloss, no gradients. The off-white background has a repeating pattern of tiny paper wave motifs in slightly darker ivory, like a watermark. Along the bottom edge, a decorative band of grey and blue paper shapes — small waves, dots, simple seaweed-like forms.

Palette: off-white (background), black (ship hull, hand, labels), red (Kyverno accent), blue (sea routes, ESO tower, ship sail), grey (port, pilot houses, secondary elements).